==English==

===Etymology===
From {{ME.}} < {{OF.}} < {{L.}} ''[[possibilis]]'' < {{L.}} ''[[posse]]'' "to be able".

===Adverb===
'''possibly'''
#of uncertain likelihood
#:''Will we win? '''Possibly'''.''
#capable of favorable outcome
#:''I'm much stronger than you, so you can't '''possibly''' win.''
#capable of being true without contradicting proven facts, laws, or circumstances
#:''I couldn't '''possibly''' be there on time.''
#capable of being done without offense to character or custom
#:''I couldn't '''possibly''' cheat on my wife.''

====Synonyms====
*(''of uncertain likelihood''): [[by chance]], [[maybe]], [[mayhap]], [[peradventure]], [[perchance]], [[perhaps]]
*(''capable of favorable outcome''): [[potentially]]
*(''capable of being true without contradiction''): [[conceivably]]
*(''capable of being done without offense''): [[conceivably]]

===Antonyms===
*(''capable of being true without contradiction''): [[impossibly]]

